article_title: Obamacare Contractor Paid 13,000 Hours Of Overtime
article_text: WASHINGTON -- The contractor who runs the Affordable Care Act application processing facility in Wentzville paid more than 13,000 hours of overtime to catch up with a backlog created by computer problems after the initial sign-up period, according to documents obtained under the Freedom of Information Act.
